<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>NURIA:  Picard, you could not save her?</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>PICARD:  No.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>NURIA:  You do have limits. You are not masters of life and death.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>PICARD:  No, we are not. We can cure many diseases and we can repair injuries, we can even extend life. But for all our knowledge, all our advances, we are just as mortal as you are. We're just as powerless to prevent the inevitable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>NURIA:  You are a remarkable people, but you are not superior beings. My people must be made to understand that.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Assembly hall</td></tr>
<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>TROI:  Liko, you don't want to kill me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>LIKO:  I have no choice. I must do as the Picard wishes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>TROI:  Are you sure you know what he wants? That's the problem with believing in a supernatural being. Trying to determine what he wants.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>LIKO:  We must do something.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>OJI:  But what if we do the wrong thing, father?</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>LIKO:  Picard, we need your guidance. Is it your wish that this woman should die? Answer us. Speak.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Picard and Nuria enter</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>PICARD:  Liko!</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>LIKO:  The Picard. The Overseer has come.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>PICARD:  No. Liko. Liko, I am a man. I am not the Overseer. I am a traveller from a faraway land. Nothing more.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>LIKO:  But you have restored my life. I am your servant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>PICARD:  You are no one's servant, Liko. I neither desire your obedience nor your worship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>NURIA:  Picard speaks the truth. I have visited his people. I have seen how they live and how they die. When death takes one of their loved ones, they are as helpless as we are.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>LIKO:  Then how was I brought back to life?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>NURIA:  Liko, you were not dead. Picard's people have a knowledge that we lack. They are able to heal wounds that we cannot.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>LIKO:  No. No. He can bring back the dead. Show them, Picard. You can bring my wife back to me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>PICARD:  I cannot.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>LIKO:  Why? Why won't you do this for me? Have I failed you in some way? Are you angry with me?</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>PICARD:  I am not angry with you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>LIKO:  Then I beg you, bring her back to me. I will give you my life in exchange. Please, take back what you gave me. Give it to her. Let her live!</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>PICARD:  It is beyond my power.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>LIKO:  Nothing is beyond your power! You are the Overseer. I will prove it!</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He aims the arrow at Picard</td></tr>

